<!--
Serbian (Latin) translation. Lives in `values-b+sr+Latn` (the BCP-47
script-qualified resource folder) rather than plain `values-sr` so
users on a Cyrillic-Serbian device locale (`sr-Cyrl`) fall through to
default English instead of being served Latin-script text. The in-app
Region picker's `Region.SR_RS` carries the matching tag `sr-Latn-RS`
so users who explicitly choose Serbian here resolve into this folder.

Tone is informal "ti"-form throughout to match the existing Croatian
register ("Ponesi …", "Obuci …"). Ekavian variant ("sneg", "verovatno",
"ovde") rather than the ijekavian forms used in values-hr — otherwise
the lexicon overlaps with Croatian heavily and we lean on that overlap
rather than maintaining two near-identical files. Scope: insight-prose
templates, garment labels, clothes-rule editor, outfit-card labels,
and region/voice-locale picker names. Other UI surfaces fall back to
default English (matching values-pl / values-uk).
-->
